Your Important Dates

These are all the dates that Time Computation has calculated for your sentence. Dates may change if you get a disciplinary infraction, or get lost time restored. Tap 'Learn More' to see what you need to do in order to be released on any date.

Standard Transition Program (TPR)
21 de diciembre de 2021
(3 años and 10 meses ago)
Release up to 90 days earlier, if you agree to attend a program in the community; must meet criteria.
Learn more about TPR
Community Supervision Begin Date (CSBD)
21 de marzo de 2022
(3 años and 7 meses ago)
Also called a Transition Release (TR) date, allows for release up to 90 days before your ERCD; must meet criteria.
Learn more about CSBD
Earned Release Credit Date (ERCD)
6 de junio de 2022
(3 años and 4 meses ago)
The earliest date you can be released based on Earned Release Credits – usually, a minimum of 85.7% of your sentence.
Learn more about ERCD
100% Date (Flat Sentence, SED)
16 de septiembre de 2022
(3 años and 1 mes ago)
The full term of your sentence; when you will be released, unless you decline conditions of supervision.
Learn more about SED
115% Date (CSED)
16 de noviembre de 2022
(2 años and 11 meses ago)
The last day that you can be under ADCRR supervision for your current sentence.
Learn more about CSED